						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Sadāśivarāya Year: Śaka 1[4]71 <hi rend="italic">saumya;</hi> 1549 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Begins with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king Sadāśivarāya, the king has <hi rend="italic">sāḷuva</hi> title. Records the supply of ghee, for the merit of Tirumalar Nāyakkar, the son . . ••••• of Nāyakkar •••• Paḍaivīḍu.</p>						

						<p>The temple accountant Vīrappaṉ ••••••ḍattūṟai Aḷgar wrote the epigraph which contains the endowment.</p>						

						</summary>
